                    <span style='font-size: 20px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'></span>The Clerkship Phase
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 3.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 20px; font-family: "Arial",sans-serif; font-style: italic;'>
                    <span style='font: size 20px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; font-style: normal;'>Years Five and Six</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <strong><span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <strong><span
                        style="font-size: 15px;">INTRODUCTION</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; font-size: 13px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; text-align: justify;'>
                    The
                    clerkship is the final phase of the undergraduate curriculum. The main goal of this phase is to
                    prepare the student for his/her future career as a successful and effective physician. &nbsp;The
                    clerkship largely consists of clinical training, hospital or health centre based, which is a
                    supervised work experience in a setting similar to the one in which the trainee will eventually
                    undertake as a physician. &nbsp; In addition to the clinical hands-on-training there will be the
                    daily afternoon interactive seminars at the College related to each of the Major Clerkship
                    rotations. &nbsp;These will be undertaken with appropriate clinicians as Tutors.
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <strong><span
                        style="font-size: 15px;">Goals of the Clerkship Phase</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <strong><span
                        style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">The central goal for the Medical Programme at AGU is to prepare the
                        student to acquire the knowledge, skills and attitude which will enable him/her &nbsp;to
                        identify, analyze and manage clinical problems in order to provide efficient, cost-effective,
                        and humane patient care.</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">These goals are expected to be achieved by going through a series of
                        different clerkship rotations. &nbsp;They are applicable to primary and secondary health care
                        delivery settings, &ldquo;Health Centers and Hospital Departments.&rdquo; &nbsp;Clearly, the
                        differences in the student&rsquo;s learning experience in different departments and settings are
                        mainly related to the nature of the health problems encountered and the available facilities and
                        expertise. The acquired competencies will constitute the framework for the development of the
                        clerkships specific objectives and are an integral part of the student assessment.</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .5in; text-indent: -.5in;'>
                    <em><span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></em>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong><span
                        style='font-size: 13px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; color: black;'>
                        <br>
                        &nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; background: white;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 15px; color: black;">General Professional Skills:</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: 200%;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 4px; line-height: 200%;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
                            &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: 200%;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 200%;">1.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;General
                            Skills</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">a)&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Information gathering (history-taking)
                            :&nbsp;</span></strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">Students should be able to obtain,
                        chart and verbally present, in a succinct manner, patient clinical histories in a way
                        appropriate to the particular clinical setting and nature of patient problems.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">b)&nbsp; &nbsp;Physical examination :</span></strong><span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;Students should be able to conduct, chart and verbally present, in
                        a systematic manner, a physical examination appropriate to the patient problems &ldquo;Focused
                        examination&rdquo;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">c)</span></strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Patient management:</strong> Students should be able to develop, chart and
                        verbally present a suitable differential diagnosis, or problem list along with appropriate
                        investigations and management plan.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">d)&nbsp; &nbsp;Communication:&nbsp;</span></strong><span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">Students should be able to use good communication skills in
                        communicating medical opinions to patients and obtaining their consent and participation in
                        management plans.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <div style='margin: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <ol start="5" style="margin-bottom: 0in; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: -0.25in;">
                        <li style='margin: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                            <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">Minor procedures :&nbsp;</span></strong><span
                               ">Students should be able to perform appropriate minor procedures
                                that are commonly performed in different clinical settings.</span></li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -5.3pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <div style='margin: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <ol start="6" style="margin-bottom: 0in; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: -0.25in;">
                        <li style='margin: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                            <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">Information retrieval, critical appraisal and
                                    evidence-based medicine:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">Students
                                should show an ability to search appropriate resources for information relevant to the
                                medical problem encountered. &nbsp;Clerks should be familiar with computer data bases
                                and various searching techniques. &nbsp;Where possible, journal articles should be
                                critically evaluated and used in practicing evidence-based medicine.</span></li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -5.3pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -5.3pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: 200%;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 200%;">2.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Professional Behavioral
                            Skills</span></strong>
                </p>
                <ol start="1" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 0in;">
                    <li><strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">Patient interaction:&nbsp;</span></strong><span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">Students should be able to interact sensitively and appropriately
                            with patients and their relatives. This should include the ability to discuss with patients
                            and their families expected levels of care such as resuscitation, other intervention,
                            palliative care, etc.</span></li>
                    <li><strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">Group interaction :&nbsp;</span></strong><span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">Students should be able to work and interact appropriately with
                            other members of the clinical team including, doctors, nurses, social workers,
                            physiotherapists, laboratory staff and other paramedical staff.</span></li>
                </ol>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <ol start="3" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: 0in;">
                    <li><strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; Self-assessment :&nbsp;</span></strong><span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">Students should demonstrate an ability to assess accurately
                            their:&nbsp;</span></li>
                </ol>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 25.85px;">
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Knowledge base and problem solving skills</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Technical skills</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Communication skills</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Professional attitudes and empathy and to develop strategies for
                            improvement as necessary</span></li>
                </ul>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: 35.45pt; text-indent: -14.15pt;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">d)</span></strong><span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Professional ethics:&nbsp;</strong>Students should
                        demonstrate an understanding and acceptance of ethical principles including:</span>
                </p>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 25.450000000000003px;">
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Respect for patients and colleagues. &nbsp;This includes respect
                            for patients&rsquo; autonomy and for their individual value systems.</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Observance of confidentiality with respect to patient
                            disclosures.</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Acceptance of the necessity for complete scientific honesty.
                            &nbsp; This includes respect for scientific truth and rejection of undue bias.</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">An awareness of frequently encountered bio-ethical decisions that
                            must be dealt with in each of the clerkship settings.</span></li>
                </ul>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 4px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 15px;">3.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Problem Solving Skills</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .5in; text-indent: -.5in;'>
                    <em><span style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span></em>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">When faced with patients, students should be able to execute all of the
                        following steps of biomedical problem-solving:</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .5in; text-indent: -.5in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
                        &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <div style='margin: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <ol start="1" style="margin-bottom: 0in; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: -0.25in;">
                        <li style='margin: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                            <span style="font-size: 13px;">Determine why the patients are seeking help,
                                (<u>PROBLEM-SENSING</u>)</span></li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">b)&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></strong><span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">Try to explain patient&rsquo;s problem, (<u>GENERATING
                            HYPOTHESES)</u></span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <div style='margin: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <ol start="3" style="margin-bottom: 0in; list-style-type: lower-alpha; margin-left: -0.25in;">
                        <li style='margin: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                            <span style="font-size: 13px;">Acquire relevant clinical data (from history, clinical exam,
                                laboratory investigation) and relevant biomedical knowledge ranging from molecular to
                                social structure and function (from educational resources). &nbsp; In doing so, students
                                should manifest <u>SELF-DIRECTED</u> <u>LEARNING ABILITY</u> (correctly identifying
                                areas of ignorance, efficiently tracking down educational resources, appropriately
                                relating new knowledge back to the patient) and competency in the <u>CRITICAL</u>
                                <u>ASSESSMENT OF EVIDENCE</u> as it relates to diagnostic, therapeutic, preventive or
                                rehabilitative measures.</span></li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">d)&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></strong><span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">Revise the list of hypotheses in light of this additional knowledge and
                        prepare a problem list and a statement of priorities, (<u>SYNTHESIS</u>).</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">e)</span></strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;Identify appropriate and cost-effective additional investigations and the options
                        for <u>MANAGEMENT</u>.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <u><span style="font-size: 11px;"><span style="text-decoration: none;">&nbsp;</span></span></u>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">f)</span></strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;
                        &nbsp;Identify residual gaps in understanding of (a) the patient, (b) the illness, (c) human
                        biology and (d) health care, (<u>EVALUATION</u>).</span>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong><span style='font-size: 15px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                        <br>
                        &nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 15px;">Guidelines To Acquiring Professional Qualities In The Clinical
                            Setting</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">A major educational objective of this program is to develop the
                        professional behavior necessary to function effectively. &nbsp; These behaviors have been
                        grouped into four areas: &nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: 53.55pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">(a) &nbsp;Respect&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
                        &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;(b) &nbsp;Communication
                        Skills</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: 35.7pt; text-indent: 17.85pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">(c) &nbsp;Responsibility&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;(d)
                        &nbsp;Self-awareness and Self-evaluation.</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: 14.2pt; text-indent: -14.2pt;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 15px;">a)</span></strong><span
                        style="font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Respect</strong></span>
                </p>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 4.199999999999999px;">
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Listen, and indicate so with appropriate verbal or non-verbal
                            behavior</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Verbal and non-verbal behavior should be neither rude, arrogant or
                            patronizing</span></li>
                </ul>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 18.35px;">
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Allow patients to express opinions and give information without
                            &ldquo;putting him or her down&rdquo;</span></li>
                </ul>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 4.199999999999999px;">
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Make explicit <strong><em>own</em></strong> assumptions regarding
                            physician-patient agenda</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Negotiate agenda with patient</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Do not interrupt patient inappropriately</span></li>
                </ul>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 18.35px;">
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Keep the focus of the interview on the patient and apologize when
                            late or give reason for being so</span></li>
                </ul>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 4.199999999999999px;">
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Maintain non-sexual behavior with patient</span></li>
                </ul>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <strong><span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: 14.2pt; text-indent: -14.2pt;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 15px;">b)&nbsp;&nbsp;Communication Skills</span></strong>
                </p>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 18.35px;">
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Speak directly to patient</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Use words patient can understand</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Present information clearly</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Give explanations clearly</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Give directions clearly</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Allow time for patient to respond</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Resolve misunderstandings</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Use open-ended questions appropriately</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Recognize and respond to patient&rsquo;s non-verbal
                            communication</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Demonstrate tolerance for silence (non-verbal behavior is
                            consistent with tone and content of verbal communication)</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Accept and discuss emotional issues</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Express own emotional state in appropriate situations</span></li>
                </ul>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: -0.5in;">
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Share with patient the logic of the progression of the
                            interview<br>
                        &nbsp;</span><strong><span style="font-size: 15px;">c)</span></strong><span
                            style="font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
                            &nbsp;<strong>Responsibility</strong></span></li>
                </ul>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 18.35px;">
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Be punctual</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Follow through on commitments made to patient</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Appear in control of own emotional state</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Explore areas relevant to patient&rsquo;s problem(s)</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Discuss management plan with patient (e.g. Lab. Work,
                            consultations, treatment)</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Provide information to enable patient to give informed
                            consent</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Provide information to enable patient to assume appropriate
                            personal responsibility for implementing and complying with management plan</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Inform patient about back-up arrangement as necessary</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Inform patient about how information yet to be obtained will be
                            conveyed to patient (e.g. From lab &nbsp;work, consultations)&nbsp;</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Consider evaluative or critical comment from supervisor, colleague
                            or patient in a non-defensive manner</span></li>
                </ul>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: 28.35pt; text-indent: -14.15pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: 14.2pt; text-indent: -14.2pt;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 15px;">d)&nbsp;&nbsp;Self-awareness &amp;
                            Self-evaluation</span></strong><strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;
                            &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 18.35px;">
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Acknowledge own difficulty in understanding</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Acknowledge own lack of appropriate knowledge</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Acknowledge own discomfort in discussing or dealing with a
                            particular issue</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Express own emotional state where appropriate</span></li>
                    <li><span style="font-size: 13px;">Consider evaluative or critical comment from supervisor, colleague
                            or patient in a non-defensive manner</span></li>
                </ul>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .5in; text-indent: -.5in;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: 35.45pt; text-indent: -35.45pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -.7pt; background: white;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 15px; color: black;">Clerkship Stresses</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -.7pt;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">The clerkship is the final step in the sequence of required learning
                        units and the medical curriculum and when the required objective are being met it should follow
                        smoothly in the same way as the preceding units. &nbsp;However, there are a number of
                        significant differences that when the students leap from a largely pre-clinical phase to the
                        clinical areas, this sometimes gives rise to a series of real or perceived stress for virtually
                        all the students in the clerkship phase. &nbsp;Awareness of some of these differences and the
                        ability to anticipate stress might help many of the students to develop strategies for coping
                        and handling them.</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">The following are some of the problems and suggested solutions:</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-left: .5in; text-indent: -.5in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 3.7pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">1.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;The transition from frequent use of paper
                        problems to constant involvement with real patient problems as the basis for clerkship education
                        brings you much closer to the realities of the medical world. &nbsp;While this may reveal some
                        of the glories of medicine, it may also expose you to the down side with its frustrations and
                        disappointments.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 3.7pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">2.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Exposure to a variety of specialty and
                        sub-specialty areas with both positive and negative role modeling by faculty clinicians
                        frequently creates tensions in those who may still be uncertain about career choices. &nbsp;For
                        example, the dilemmas around<em>&nbsp;&ldquo;I like everything I see; what should I
                            choose?&rdquo;</em> or <em>&ldquo;will I be satisfied working in a somewhat narrowed
                            subspecialty area?&rdquo;</em> are very real issues.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 3.7pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: 14.2pt; text-indent: -14.2pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 3.7pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">3.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Clerks are always concerned about expectations of
                        them by faculty and patients as they assume responsibility for patient care and this introduces
                        a new level of stress and uneasiness. &nbsp;While this is realistic preparation for functioning
                        in the &ldquo;real world&rdquo;, the constant tension between service and educational
                        obligations is pervasive. &nbsp; The overriding principle in clerkship must be one that ensures
                        that the service role will be considered valid only where related educational benefits are
                        evident.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: 3.7pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 3.7pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">4.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Perhaps more so than in prior curriculum units
                        there is a need to appear competent both in your own eyes, and in those of your peers and
                        faculty. While this is likely a natural tendency in everyone&rsquo;s personal and professional
                        development, at times it may interfere with a simultaneous need to express feelings of
                        vulnerability, uncertainty, fear or confusion about competence, and about career direction.
                        &nbsp;This incongruity between outward display and inner needs may be a further source of stress
                        for you.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 3.7pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: 14.2pt; text-indent: -14.2pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 3.7pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">5.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Concurrent with all of the above tensions in
                        clerkship is the unavoidable activity, often fraught with roadblocks, related to your preparing
                        for the final MD. Examinations, applying for internship, arranging interviews, etc.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 3.7pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: 14.2pt; text-indent: -14.2pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -5.3pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">Given all of the above how can students in the clerkship phase deal
                        with some of these unavoidable stress factors? &nbsp;The following are some of the available
                        remedies.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -5.3pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -5.3pt;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 15px;">Student Advisor System</span></strong><span
                        style="font-size: 15px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -5.3pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">Student advisors can often play an important role in clerkship, and
                        yet are very frequently underutilized by students at this point in the Program. There is a
                        perception among students that disclosure of personal concerns or the need to ventilate about
                        them will be perceived as a sign of weakness. Students may therefore avoid doing so at all
                        costs, for fear that it may appear in the final evaluation. &nbsp;There is no evidence to
                        support this fear; in fact the ability to accurately assess one&rsquo;s own circumstances and a
                        willingness to seek counsel should be perceived as strength.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -5.3pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">Each student in the clerkship phase will be assigned to an academic
                        advisor who will follow the students&rsquo; academic performance and act as his/her
                        advocate.</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-top: 0in; margin-right: -5.3pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: 13.5pt; text-indent: -13.5pt;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -5.3pt;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -5.3pt;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; background: white;'>
                    <strong><span style="font-size: 15px; color: black;">Assessment and
                            Evaluation</span></strong><strong><span style="font-size: 13px; color: black;">&nbsp;in the
                            Clerkship</span></strong>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">Evaluation continues to be central to gaining competence in clinical
                        medicine. &nbsp; Specifically, <u>self-evaluation</u> should become part of your daily routine
                        in this unit because it will, in time, constitute about the only feedback you will receive later
                        in your clinical career.&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p
                    style='margin: 0in; text-align: justify; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif; margin-right: -.8pt;'>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">Operationally, both students and tutors are jointly collecting,
                        collating and synthesizing evaluation data and letting the College know how things are going
                        with students, faculty and the whole program. It is crucial, therefore, that you sort out, early
                        in each rotation, how and from whom you will obtain data and whether the clerkship objectives
                        are being met. &nbsp; Thus the evaluation processes which are applied during the clerkship phase
                        are of three types -</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">Evaluation of:</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 11px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <ul style="list-style-type: undefined; margin-left: 4.15px;">
                    <li><strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">student performance by faculty</span></strong></li>
                    <li><strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">the faculty and clinical instructors performance by
                                students</span></strong></li>
                    <li><strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">the clerkship programme and implementation by student and
                                faculty</span></strong></li>
                </ul>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">&nbsp;</span>
                </p>
                <p style='margin: 0in; text-align: left; font-size: 17px; font-family: "Times New Roman",serif;'>
                    <span
                        style="font-size: 13px;">The process of evaluation is described in detail later in this
                        handbook.</span>
                </p>

